hematically, the correspondence covers a wide range of political, cultural, and social topics, including the Cold War, the Korean War, the role of Christians in mediating dialogue between East and West, McCarthyism, and topics focused on the internal politics of Czechoslovakia.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCold War. 4aBriefe. 4aKalter Krieg. 4aKommunismus. 4aMcCarthyism. 4aTschechoslowakei. 4aVereinigte Staaten. 7aHISTORY / Military / Wars & Conflicts (Other).2bisacsh  aCold War.  aCzechoslovakia.  aMcCarthyism.  aUnited States.  aletters.1 aOlšáková, Doubravka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z97831107668200 cEPUBz97831106905450 cprintz978311069040840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311069050740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110690507423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110690507/original  a978-3-11-076682-0  DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK